I love how this doujin shows what would happen if everything that could possibly go right given a kidnapping actually went right. Like I could totally see the "decent guy kidnapper with good intentions" as a believable character and maybe even akin to how people (particularly kidnappers) actually are irl. Plus it just happened that the girl's life was full of familiarity with sex and loneliness, hence why she'd even agree to do something like this in the first place. Everything that could happen, happened in this case and that isn't impossible. Pretty cool work Ichihaya, though I do feel a bit guilty reading this for some reason lol.
